  "prompt": "I am working in ZS Associates as a Technology analyst. I do not like the work-life imbalance. Should I go for SSC CGL or switch to other private firm?",
  "response": "Here are some considerations to help you decide:\n\nSSC CGL Pros:\n1. Government job security\n2. Fixed working hours\n3. Good pension and benefits\n4. Stable career path\n5. Respectful social status\n6. Lower stress levels\n\nSSC CGL Cons:\n1. Competitive exam\n2. Lower initial salary\n3. Slower career growth\n4. Less dynamic work environment\n\nAlternative Private Firms Pros:\n1. Potentially better work culture\n2. Higher salary potential\n3. More dynamic roles\n4. Technology-focused opportunities\n5. Faster career progression\n\nAlternative Private Firms Cons:\n1. Less job security\n2. Potential work-life balance issues\n\nRecommendations:\n1. First, analyze your current role at ZS Associates\n- Discuss work-life balance with manager\n- Explore internal role/team changes\n- Understand growth opportunities\n\n2. Research alternative IT/tech companies\n- Product-based companies\n- Startups\n- Companies with good work culture\n\n3. Prepare for SSC CGL simultaneously\n- Part-time preparation\n- Keep options open\n\n4. Network and explore opportunities\n- LinkedIn\n- Job portals\n- Referrals\n\nFinal decision depends on:\n- Personal career goals\n- Financial stability\n- Long-term aspirations",
